import matplotlib.patches as mpatches
import albumentations as album

def crop_image(image, true_dimensions):
    return album.CenterCrop(p=1, height=true_dimensions[0], width=true_dimensions[1])(image=image)['image']


# helper function for data visualization
def visualize(**images):

    n_images = len(images)
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,12))
    for idx, (name, image) in enumerate(images.items()):
        plt.subplot(1, n_images, idx + 1)
        plt.xticks([]); 
        plt.yticks([])
        # get title from the parameter names
        plt.title(name.replace('_',' ').title(), fontsize=20)
        plt.imshow(image)
    plt.show()


# Perform one hot encoding on labeled semantic image
def one_hot_encode(img, palette):
  semantic_map = []
  for color in palette:
    class_map = tf.reduce_all(tf.equal(img, color), axis=-1)
    semantic_map.append(class_map)
  semantic_map = tf.stack(semantic_map, axis=-1)
  # casting to float 32
  semantic_map = tf.cast(semantic_map, tf.float32)
  return semantic_map


def reverse_one_hot(img):
  x = np.argmax(img, axis = -1)
  return x


#converting one hot colors back to original int representation
def color_segmentation(img, palette):
  colors = np.array(palette)
  reversed = colors[img.astype(int)]
  return reversed


# Plot a confusion matrix.
# cm is the confusion matrix, names are the names of the classes.
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, names, title='Confusion matrix', cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(names))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, names, rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, names)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')

def hms_string(sec_elapsed):
    h = int(sec_elapsed / (60 * 60))
    m = int((sec_elapsed % (60 * 60)) / 60)
    s = sec_elapsed % 60
    return "{}:{:>02}:{:>05.2f}".format(h, m, s)

# creating a class for the dataset
# this class will read images and resize them
from PIL import Image, ImageOps, ImageChops
from numpy import expand_dims
from keras.preprocessing.image import load_img
from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from random import randrange

image_size = (320,320)

class DataSet():

  def __init__(self, df, class_rgb_values=None):
    self.image_paths = df['image_path'].tolist()
    self.mask_paths = df['label_colored_path'].tolist()
    self.class_rgb_values = class_rgb_values
    self.image_width = df['image_width'].tolist()
    self.image_height = df['image_height'].tolist()


  def __getitem__(self, i):
        
    # read images, resize and pad to size of 320,320
    image = Image.open('../tmp/' + self.image_paths[i])
    image = ImageOps.pad(image, image_size, color='black')
    

    # read masks, resize and pad to size of 320,320
    mask = Image.open('../tmp/' + self.mask_paths[i])
    mask = ImageOps.pad(mask, image_size, color='black')

    image, mask = self.preprocess_image(image, mask)

    # convert resized image to np array
    image = np.array(image)
    mask = np.array(mask)

    # one-hot-encode the mask
    mask = one_hot_encode(mask, self.class_rgb_values)
  
    return image, mask


  def preprocess_image(self, image, mask):
    rand_int_4 = randrange(4)
    if rand_int_4 == 0:
      image = ImageOps.flip(image)
      mask = ImageOps.flip(mask)

    elif rand_int_4 == 1:
      image = ImageOps.mirror(image)
      mask = ImageOps.mirror(mask)

    elif rand_int_4 == 2:
      image = ImageOps.flip(image)
      image = ImageOps.mirror(image)
      mask = ImageOps.flip(mask)
      mask = ImageOps.mirror(mask)

    return image, mask


  def __len__(self):
    # return length of 
    return len(self.image_paths)

# transfer learning using VGG16
# creating VGG16 encoder using 
from tensorflow.keras.applications.vgg16 import VGG16
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model, Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, Activation, Flatten
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, Conv2DTranspose, Concatenate, BatchNormalization, Input, ZeroPadding2D

# creates convolutional block and returns last layer
def conv_block(inputs, num_filters):
  x = Conv2D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(inputs)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  x = Conv2D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)
  return x

# creates decoder block to upsample image
def decoder_block(inputs=None, skip_features=None, num_filters=64):
  x = Conv2DTranspose(num_filters, (2,2), strides=2, padding="same")(inputs)
  if skip_features == None:
    x = conv_block(x, num_filters)
  else:
    x = Concatenate()([x, skip_features])
    x = conv_block(x, num_filters)
  return x


def build_vgg16(input_shape):
  inputs = Input(shape=input_shape)
  vgg16 = VGG16(include_top=False, weights='imagenet', input_shape=input_shape, input_tensor=inputs)
 
  #freeze top layers so the weights dont change
  vgg16.trainable=False
  
  # skip connections: using output of these VGG16 layers as input to next layer
  s1 = vgg16.get_layer("block1_conv2").output #512
  s2 = vgg16.get_layer("block2_conv2").output #256
  s3 = vgg16.get_layer("block3_conv3").output #128
  s4 = vgg16.get_layer("block4_conv3").output #64

  
  # bridge layer between encoder and decoder
  # defines how to pass encoder states to decoder
  b1 = vgg16.get_layer("block5_conv3").output #32

  # decode blocks
  d1 = decoder_block(b1, s4, 512)
  d2 = decoder_block(d1, s3, 256)
  d3 = decoder_block(d2, s2, 128)
  d4 = decoder_block(d3, s1, 64)

  outputs = Conv2D(9, 1, activation='softmax')(d4)

  model = Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=outputs, name="VGG16net")
  return model

# creating custom model 2

def create_model2():

  model2_inputs = Input(shape=(320,320,3))
  
  # conv block 1
  x = Conv2D(64, 3, padding="same")(model2_inputs)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  x = Conv2D(64, 3, padding="same", name="conv1")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)
  
  #conv block 2
  x = Conv2D(128, 3, padding="same")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  x = Conv2D(128, 3, padding="same", name="conv2")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  #conv block 3
  x = Conv2D(256, 3, padding="same")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  x = Conv2D(256, 3, padding="same", name="conv3")(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x)
  x = Activation("relu")(x)

  x = decoder_block(x, None, 256)
  x = decoder_block(x, None, 128)
  x = decoder_block(x, None, 64)

  outputs = Conv2D(9, 1, activation='softmax')(x)

  model2 = Model(inputs=model2_inputs, outputs = outputs)
  model2.summary()
  return model2
